title: 'PITFALL: One seems to have to read the whole thing, not just the backward incompatibilities section.'
pid: fc89d4aa-0827-47ab-b715-4fc2fe7ffa66
body: |2-
  While trying to migrate to 21.05, I'm also reading
  "B.1.4. Other Notable Changes",
  because it starts by saying that stdenv.lib will break.
